{
  "explanation": "The defendant committed a breach of professional trust while acting as an accountant by embezzling $25,000. While the defendant has no prior criminal history and has made a partial restitution, which demonstrates remorse and an effort to rectify the harm, a fiduciary violation of this nature warrants a period of incarceration to serve as a deterrent and acknowledge the severity of the betrayal of confidence. A sentence of 6 months reflects the balance between these mitigating factors and the underlying crime.",
  "verdict": 6
}
